# In-container cron schedule, run by supercronic. Each line is a standard
# cron expression followed by a command. Output goes to stdout/stderr,
# which Fly captures into ``fly logs``.
#
# Format: minute hour day-of-month month day-of-week command
#
# Defensive wrappers:
#   * ``flock -n`` skips this tick if a previous one is still running,
#     preventing process pile-up when a tick takes longer than its
#     interval (e.g. TfL API slow).
#   * ``timeout 240`` kills any tick that exceeds 4 minutes, so a hung
#     HTTP call doesn't tie up a worker forever.
# Both are standard Debian binaries already in the slim image.

*/5 * * * * /usr/bin/flock -n /tmp/update_incidents.lock /usr/bin/timeout 240 /opt/venv/bin/python -m django update_incidents --settings=updown.settings
